node.text: @hazeldiary_ 👍🏼 really shiok! Say yes to cheese 😂
i love all the one pan dishes! 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

Presenting my one pan { Dak-galbi } aka korean spicy stir fried chicken. Can you tell I’m missing Korea ?! This is also this week’s #cbfoodiesg ‘s theme - chicken and only two of us are taking part ( some unforeseen situation came up for the other 2 kaki 🤣) .
Main ingredients for this dish are chicken , sweet potato , cabbage and rice cake to name some. It is basically a communal dish and it comes serve in a pan with stove on the table so you can cook it yourselves or have the staff cook on the spot for you.
.
You can add rice to it once you are 80 % done. The staff can whip up a fried rice with whatever that’s left in the pan.
.
So yeah here’s my own rendition with kale on the sides for some color :D added cheese as well 🤤🤤😋😋 want some ? Let’s cheers over soju !! 🍶🥂🍷🍾🍻 #sgunited#stayhomesg#
@msoinkee cheers !!
@eileen_eats_alot 🥂
@fatwithin Chop marinate and throw everything in 😂
@eileen_eats_alot best way to cook😂
Nice work!😋
@mshannahchia very simple de ! Chop, marinate and throw everything into the pan 😀
@eileen_eats_alot i like simple cooking cos i am a lazy home cook. Hahaahahs
Good idea. I shall try next time😍
@crappysotong I mean lotsa lotsa cheese haha
@crappysotong hahaha oops that didn’t happen but this is good ! Make it : D with lots of cheese !
Haha it was what I wanted to do for the korean challenge but with cheese ! Haha yum
@foodieislegal is fun eating this in Korea
Wow I miss korea! Always craving for korean food! 😍
@leenchong same I miss korea food !
looks good!!! i am missing tis too!😃
@aprilyap thanks Heheeh hearty pan ! I like
Looks really good!😍
@shootandspoon is easy to make this dish !
Looks really good 😋, drooling 🤤
